of yours of closely observing others.

23
00:03:31.544 --> 00:03:36.007 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
Sorry. But you’re easy to figure out
even without observing closely.

24
00:03:36.090 --> 00:03:37.550 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
I don’t want you figuring me out!

25
00:03:38.551 --> 00:03:39.802 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
But I can.

26
00:03:41.554 --> 00:03:42.889 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
It’s dangerous here.

27
00:03:42.972 --> 00:03:46.601 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
Looking at the night sky,
it’s as if you can reach the stars.

28
00:03:47.352 --> 00:03:49.562 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
You get the feeling that
your dreams will come true.

29
00:03:52.690 --> 00:03:55.526 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
<i>Shin, thank you for your email.</i>

30
00:03:56.194 --> 00:04:01.157 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
<i>I feel it’s been a long time</i>
<i>since I’ve seen that many stars.</i>

31
00:04:02.742 --> 00:04:04.327 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
<i>Even if I close my eyes,</i>

32
00:04:04.410 --> 00:04:08.873 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
<i>I can only imagine artificial neon lights</i>
<i>like in a planetarium.</i>

33
00:04:09.832 --> 00:04:14.045 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:10.00% 
<i>Because I thought I’m no different</i>
<i>from such neon lights.</i>

34
00:04:14.128 --> 00:04:18.299 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:10.00% 
<i>Your words have saved me once again, Shin.</i>

35
00:04:18.383 --> 00:04:20.551 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
<i>Thank you so much.</i>

36
00:04:27.141 --> 00:04:28.893 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
PHEW

37
00:04:28.977 --> 00:04:31.980 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
Thank you, Nami. You have quite the tan.

38
00:04:32.063 --> 00:04:34.857 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
No! Yes! I mean,
I’m sorry, I’m kind of nervous!

39
00:04:34.941 --> 00:04:37.777 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
I’ve been a big fan of Trapnest
since your debut!

40
00:04:37.860 --> 00:04:38.861 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
Really?

41
00:04:38.945 --> 00:04:41.406 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
Don’t question her. She’s being polite.

42
00:04:42.448 --> 00:04:43.283 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
Honey!

43
00:04:43.366 --> 00:04:45.743 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
You think this pattern is too flashy?

44
00:04:45.827 --> 00:04:47.912 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
You don’t need to wear a tie.

45
00:04:47.996 --> 00:04:51.082 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
I have to look dignified as a father.

46
00:04:51.165 --> 00:04:53.626 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
Sorry to keep you waiting!

47
00:04:57.922 --> 00:04:59.799 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
Pleased to meet you. I’m Takumi Ichinose.

48
00:04:59.882 --> 00:05:01.676 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
You sure are tall! H-- How tall are you?

49
00:05:01.759 --> 00:05:04.178 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
One meter and 83 centimeters, right?

50
00:05:04.262 --> 00:05:08.182 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
I wasn’t asking you. Fawning all over him…

51
00:05:08.891 --> 00:05:12.437 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
I apologize that it took so long
before I could come.

52
00:05:12.520 --> 00:05:14.314 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
These are some gifts from England.

53
00:05:14.397 --> 00:05:17.525 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
Though, the only thing British
about them is the tea.

54
00:05:17.608 --> 00:05:19.485 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
-Oh my, this much?
-What is it?

55
00:05:19.569 --> 00:05:22.989 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
Wow, thanks, Brother!
I’ll follow you for the rest of my life!

56
00:05:23.072 --> 00:05:24.324 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
How cozy!

57
00:05:24.407 --> 00:05:28.745 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
It’s beautiful! Your father
would never buy me things like this.

58
00:05:29.370 --> 00:05:31.706 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
You certainly seem to be well-off,
Mr. Ichinose.

59
00:05:31.789 --> 00:05:35.585 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
Do celebrities get paid that well?

60
00:05:35.668 --> 00:05:37.128 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
It depends on the person.

61
00:05:37.211 --> 00:05:39.338 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
After all, your profits are determined
by your popularity.

62
00:05:39.422 --> 00:05:40.423 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
That’s true.

63
00:05:40.506 --> 00:05:43.051 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
Are you sure you can provide
for my daughter and her child

64
00:05:43.134 --> 00:05:45.094 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
for the rest of their lives?

65
00:05:45.178 --> 00:05:47.346 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
-I’m positive, sir.
-<i>"Sir "?</i>

66
00:05:47.430 --> 00:05:49.724 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
<i>He seems like an untrustworthy guy.</i>

67
00:05:49.807 --> 00:05:54.270 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
I may be a celebrity on the outside,
but I’m just a hard worker.

68
00:05:54.896 --> 00:06:00.109 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
It’s difficult to continue a band
regardless of its popularity.

69
00:06:00.193 --> 00:06:03.196 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
I’d like to be in the same band forever,

70
00:06:03.279 --> 00:06:05.531 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
but that’s not something that
I alone can determine.

71
00:06:08.534 --> 00:06:14.415 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:10.00% 
<i>Today, I wore a wedding dress</i>
<i>while filming our promo video.</i>

72
00:06:14.499 --> 00:06:16.667 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:10.00% 
<i>It’s a song about a woman</i>
<i>who can’t get married.</i>

73
00:06:16.751 --> 00:06:19.462 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:10.00% 
<i>The staff just don't get it!</i>

74
00:06:20.296 --> 00:06:25.593 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:10.00% 
<i>We filmed the entire day for a few scenes</i>
<i>that will only be a few seconds.</i>

75
00:06:25.676 --> 00:06:27.637 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:10.00% 
<i>Everything we work on is like that.</i>

76
00:06:27.720 --> 00:06:30.515 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:10.00% 
<i>The work takes a lot of effort,</i>

77
00:06:30.598 --> 00:06:34.852 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:10.00% 
<i>but the thrill of completing something</i>
<i>together is like none other,</i>

78
00:06:34.936 --> 00:06:39.232 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:10.00% 
<i>and with my friends,</i>
<i>I’m able to feel that I belong here.</i>

79
00:06:39.315 --> 00:06:41.651 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:10.00% 
<i>Thinking back, that’s probably</i>
<i>why I was able to come this far</i>

80
00:06:41.734 --> 00:06:44.445 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
<i>with my singing</i>
<i>no matter how tough things got.</i>

81
00:06:45.029 --> 00:06:47.156 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
All right, okay. We’re done.

82
00:06:47.240 --> 00:06:50.118 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
-Done already?
-We’ve done enough.

83
00:06:50.201 --> 00:06:51.828 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
At your current level as a singer,

84
00:06:51.911 --> 00:06:53.913 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
it’ll be the same, no matter
how many times we record.

85
00:06:53.996 --> 00:06:57.500 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
In other words, you’ve given it
all you’ve got for now, and it was great.

86
00:06:57.583 --> 00:06:58.876 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
What’s that supposed to mean?

87
00:06:59.502 --> 00:07:03.089 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
We can artificially adjust the high notes
you have trouble reaching.

88
00:07:03.172 --> 00:07:04.674 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
Do some voice training
before the live performance,

89
00:07:04.757 --> 00:07:05.883 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
so you don’t embarrass yourself.

90
00:07:05.967 --> 00:07:09.428 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
Otherwise, the music magazines
will start writing nasty things about you.

91
00:07:09.512 --> 00:07:11.889 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
Shut up! Stop laughing!
Let me sing it again!

92
00:07:12.849 --> 00:07:15.685 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
Well then, now that we’re done
with the recording,

93
00:07:15.768 --> 00:07:16.978 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
what do you say we go fishing?

94
00:07:17.061 --> 00:07:19.021 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
-Yeah, that sounds like fun.
-All right!

95
00:07:19.105 --> 00:07:21.524 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
That’s the only thing I’ve been looking
forward to doing here.

96
00:07:21.607 --> 00:07:23.276 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
-The only thing?
-Matsuo!

97
00:07:23.359 --> 00:07:25.153 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
Let me sing some more!

98
00:07:25.236 --> 00:07:27.447 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
Keep it down!
You’ll scare off all the fish!

99
00:07:27.530 --> 00:07:29.198 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
Say, why did your wife leave you?

100
00:07:29.282 --> 00:07:30.450 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
Um…

101
00:07:30.533 --> 00:07:34.871 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
<i>I think the number one reason Gaia</i>
<i>decided to record at that training camp</i>

102
00:07:34.954 --> 00:07:39.125 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:10.00% 
<i>was to strengthen the bond</i>
<i>between the band members and the staff.</i>

103
00:07:39.208 --> 00:07:42.837 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
<i>The staff you’ll be working</i>
<i>with from now on</i>

104
00:07:42.920 --> 00:07:47.008 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:10.00% 
<i>will be like your family,</i>
<i>there to support the band.</i>

105
00:07:47.091 --> 00:07:51.429 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:10.00% 
<i>I think participating in that camp</i>
<i>has great meaning to it.</i>

106
00:07:52.263 --> 00:07:54.682 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
<i>Let’s both do our best.</i>

107
00:07:55.433 --> 00:07:57.727 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
Mr. Ichinose, what about your family?

108
00:07:57.810 --> 00:07:58.895 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
How many siblings do you have?

109
00:07:58.978 --> 00:08:00.897 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
You have a big sister, right?

110
00:08:00.980 --> 00:08:02.815 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
We’re not asking you.

111
00:08:02.899 --> 00:08:03.900 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
Honey…

112
00:08:03.983 --> 00:08:06.986 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
Would you let me talk too?
This isn’t any fun!

113
00:08:07.069 --> 00:08:10.114 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
But you hardly know a damn thing
about my family, don't you?

114
00:08:10.198 --> 00:08:12.283 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
-"A damn thing"?
-Excuse my language.

115
00:08:12.366 --> 00:08:13.534 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
Oh, that’s not a problem at all!

116
00:08:13.618 --> 00:08:15.870 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
You can use that language with me
whenever you damn please!

117
00:08:15.953 --> 00:08:18.539 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
It’s not fine! Not at all!
And your Japanese is funny!

118
00:08:18.623 --> 00:08:21.417 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
Nami, go buy some sake.

119
00:08:21.501 --> 00:08:22.335 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
Yes, you do that.

120
00:08:22.418 --> 00:08:23.920 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
And pick up the ingredients
for sukiyaki too.

121
00:08:24.003 --> 00:08:26.756 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
Huh? No way!
Besides, what are the ingredients? Meat?

122
00:08:26.839 --> 00:08:28.966 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
Let’s take the car
and go together, Nami. Okay?

123
00:08:29.050 --> 00:08:31.052 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
You wanna go out
with your new handbag, don’t you?

124
00:08:32.136 --> 00:08:35.765 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
Don’t tell me you like Nami.
Please, anyone but her.

125
00:08:35.848 --> 00:08:40.061 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
I’m so sorry! Nana and Nami
are both such noisy girls.

126
00:08:40.144 --> 00:08:42.897 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
Me too? Don’t group me with Nami!

127
00:08:42.980 --> 00:08:44.524 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
Not at all. I’m enjoying this very much.

128
00:08:44.607 --> 00:08:46.901 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
My mother was very weak,

129
00:08:46.984 --> 00:08:49.237 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
and the rest of my family
was rather gloomy.

130
00:08:49.320 --> 00:08:50.238 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
Perhaps because of that,

131
00:08:50.321 --> 00:08:53.282 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
I’ve always been drawn
to energetic, happy people.

132
00:08:54.617 --> 00:08:57.161 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
<i>That’s why I find this so attractive.</i>

133
00:08:57.245 --> 00:09:02.375 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
<i>The feeling of a loving family</i>
<i>like yours. This is fun.</i>

134
00:09:04.669 --> 00:09:05.795 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
I see.

135
00:09:05.878 --> 00:09:09.257 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
Well, one thing I can guarantee
is Nana’s good health.

136
00:09:09.340 --> 00:09:11.300 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
So how is your family doing now?

137
00:09:11.384 --> 00:09:14.095 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
My mother passed away six years ago.

138
00:09:14.178 --> 00:09:16.430 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
My sister married a local man.

139
00:09:16.514 --> 00:09:19.183 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
They now live
